Bury St. Edmonds Woman, in Suffolk, she is now in the Wards of the Fleet Prison, The Warden sent for her one Day to pay her Chamber-Rent, she Ask'd him how much she must pay a Week? He tells her, Six Shillings a Week; she told him it was too much, she could not pay it;
The Warden Answered, It was the Rate the Judges had set on that Chamber, and if they had not set a Rate, he would have Sixteen Shillings a Week for that Chamber, for he would make what he pleased of his own.
